The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves learning a scoring model and optimization procedures, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on coordination and assignment of agents to tasks suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning and optimization techniques to solve coordination problems in complex environments suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
